= lesson 24: body

We already know the words for #emph[eyes], #emph[heart], #emph[face], and
#emph[back], so let's learn the remaining parts of the body!

#list((
  word("REPLACE", "lawa", "head; to lead"),
  word("REPLACE", "kute", "ear; to hear"),
  word("REPLACE", "nena", "bump, like a nose, hill, breast"),
  word("REPLACE", "uta", "mouth, lips; to kiss, to bite"),
  word("REPLACE", "sijelo", "body"),
  word("REPLACE", "luka", "hand, arm; to touch"),
  word("REPLACE", "noka", "foot, leg"),
  word("REPLACE", "palisa", "long hard thing, like a branch, rod, staff"),
  word("REPLACE", "linja", "long flexible thing, like a string, rope"),
))

Something fun to notice is how many parts of the body have an associated action!
The head leads, the eyes see, the ears hear, the mouth kisses, the heart feels,
the hands touch.

